The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 24: Tata Autocomp Systems Ltd (Taco) today said it would acquire the business and assets of Wundsch Weidinger, a German automotive components supplier, for an undisclosed sum. The German firm, which makes functional plastic parts and systems for the automotive industry, had 270 employees. It had filed for insolvency in March, Taco said. The acquisition would be made through Taco?s 100 per cent subsidiary, which was set up in Germany.

 Chennai, Aug. 24: The National Iranian Oil Co today ruled out selling its 15.40 per cent stake in Chennai Petroleum Corporation Ltd. It is also not in favour of Chennai Petro?s merger with Indian Oil Corporation.

 New Delhi, Aug. 24: Pension funds may be barred from investing the hard-earned money of Indians in foreign securities, said D. Swarup, chairman of the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 24: The National Housing Bank today cancelled the licence of ailing SBI Home Finance, a subsidiary of the State Bank of India.

 New Delhi, Aug. 24: The government has extended the term of an expert committee set up to formulate an integrated energy policy, till October, power minister P.M. Sayeed said today.




